First, we need to sketch a diagram to visualize the problem. Draw a square ABCD with side length 2. Then, draw a semicircle inside the square with diameter AB. Let the tangent from C to the semicircle intersect the side AD at point E.

[asy]
pair A,B,C,D,I;
I=(0,2.5);
A=(0,0);
B=(10,0);
C=(10,10);
D=(0,10);
draw((5,5)..A--B..cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw(C--I,linewidth(0.7));
draw(A--B--C--D--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$C$",C,NE);
label("$D$",D,NW);
label("$E$",I,W);
